domestic workers, or maids,

29
00:01:41,840 --> 00:01:43,400
working in Singapore,

30
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:47,520
they have become an essential
part of the Singaporean household.

31
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:49,520
But a recent survey has shown that

32
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:51,560
many Singaporean parents

33
00:01:51,560 --> 00:01:54,920
are becoming increasingly worried
with the idea

34
00:01:54,920 --> 00:01:58,480
that their children are being
parented by their maids.

35
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:02,320
I first noticed it during
dinner last week.

36
00:02:02,320 --> 00:02:06,080
I was sending out an urgent email
at 11 p.m. to my subordinates

37
00:02:06,080 --> 00:02:08,560
about the virtues of
work-life compromise

38
00:02:08,560 --> 00:02:10,920
when my 2-year-old suddenly
shouted, “Mama!”

39
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:12,520
At first, I was going to
ask him to shut up

40
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:14,000
because I thought he
was disturbing me.

41
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,320
But then when I turned around,

42
00:02:15,920 --> 00:02:17,640
I saw that he was calling
out to my helper!

43
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:21,040
